"Specifying a distance of 3 would cause the segment ``[0 0] -> [10 0]`` to"
" be converted to ``[0 0] -> [2.5 0] -> [5 0] -> [7.5 0] -> [10 0]``, "
"since 3 extra vertices are required on the segment and spacing these at "
"2.5 increments allows them to be evenly spaced over the segment."
