#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:2084
msgid "Dissolve"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:2085
msgid ""
"Takes a vector layer and combines its features into new features. One or "
"more attributes can be specified to dissolve features belonging to the "
"same class (having the same value for the specified attributes), "
"alternatively all features can be dissolved to a single feature."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:2091
msgid ""
"All output geometries will be converted to multi geometries. In case the "
"input is a polygon layer, common boundaries of adjacent polygons being "
"dissolved will get erased. If enabled, the optional \"Keep disjoint "
"features separate\" setting will cause features and parts that do not "
"overlap or touch to be exported as separate features (instead of parts of"
" a single multipart feature)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:2098
msgid ""
"The resulting attribute table will have the same fields as the input "
"layer. The values in the output layer's fields are the ones of the first "
"input feature that happens to be processed."
msgstr ""

